natural_language_question:
For a given lipid (SWISSLIPID:000399814, Ceramide), return a list of all enzymes in UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot annotated to catalyze reactions involving that lipid.
This query does not consider the hierarchy: it looks for reactions and enzymes only for the specified lipid.
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX SWISSLIPID: <https://swisslipids.org/rdf/SLM_>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>

# Example 16
SELECT ?startId ?startName ?uniprot
WHERE
{
  # SwissLipids query (list of) identifier(s)
  VALUES ?startId { SWISSLIPID:000399814 }
  # name
  ?startId rdfs:label ?startName .
  # ChEBI x-ref
  ?startId owl:equivalentClass ?chebi .
  # federated query to Rhea
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
  	?rhea rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound/rh:chebi ?chebi .
  }    
  # federated query to UniProt
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    ?uniprot up:reviewed true .
    ?uniprot up:annotation/up:catalyticActivity/up:catalyzedReaction ?rhea .
  }
} 
ORDER BY ?startId

    ?uniprot up:reviewed true .

natural_language_question:
For a given lipid (SWISSLIPID:000399814, Ceramide), return a list of all corresponding reactions (Rhea IDs and equation).
This query does consider the hierarchy: it looks for reactions involving the specified lipid and/or its more specific forms.
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX SWISSLIPID: <https://swisslipids.org/rdf/SLM_>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>

# Example 5
SELECT ?startId ?startName ?id ?name ?chebi ?rhea ?rheaEquation 
WHERE
{
  # SwissLipids query (list of) identifier(s)
  VALUES ?startId { SWISSLIPID:000399814 }
  # name
  ?startId rdfs:label ?startName .
  # Retrieve children lipids 
  ?id rdfs:subClassOf* ?startId .
  ?id rdfs:label ?name .
  # ChEBI x-ref
  ?id owl:equivalentClass ?chebi .
  # federated query to Rhea
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
  	?rhea rh:equation ?rheaEquation .
  	?rhea rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound/rh:chebi ?chebi .
  }    
} 
ORDER BY  ?startId ?id
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.swisslipids.org/sparql/
PREFIX SWISSLIPID: <https://swisslipids.org/rdf/SLM_>
PREFIX owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>

SELECT DISTINCT ?rheaId ?equation
WHERE {
  # Start with the given SwissLipids ID
  VALUES ?swisslipid { SWISSLIPID:000399814 }

  # Find the equivalent ChEBI ID in SwissLipids
  # SwissLipids links to ChEBI using owl:equivalentClass
  ?swisslipid owl:equivalentClass ?chebi .

  # Federated query to Rhea to find reactions involving the lipid or its descendants
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    # Find all ChEBI entities that are the lipid (?chebi) or its descendants in the hierarchy
    # rdfs:subClassOf* includes the starting node itself
    ?descendantChebi rdfs:subClassOf* ?chebi .

    # Find Rhea reactions involving these descendant ChEBI entities
    # A compound in Rhea can link to ChEBI in several ways (chebi, reactivePart/chebi, underlyingChebi/chebi)
    ?rhea rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound ?compound .
    { ?compound rh:chebi ?descendantChebi }
    UNION
    { ?compound rh:reactivePart/rh:chebi ?descendantChebi }
    UNION
    { ?compound rh:underlyingChebi/rh:chebi ?descendantChebi }

    # Get the Rhea ID and equation for the found reactions
    ?rhea rh:accession ?rheaId .
    ?rhea rh:equation ?equation .
  }
}
ORDER BY ?rheaId

                                 up:catalyticActivity ?catalyticActivity .

  SERVICE <https://sparql.swisslipids.org/sparql/> {

natural_language_question: What are the Homo sapiens genes associated with cancer and their orthologs expressed in the Rattus norvegicus brain?
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql/
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX orthodb: <http://purl.orthodb.org/>
PREFIX genex: <http://purl.org/genex#>
PREFIX lscr: <http://purl.org/lscr#>

SELECT DISTINCT ?humanGeneName ?ratProtein
WHERE {
  # Find human proteins (Homo sapiens)
  ?humanProtein a up:Protein ;
                up:organism taxon:9606 ; # Homo sapiens
                up:annotation ?diseaseAnnotation .

  # Filter for proteins associated with diseases related to cancer
  ?diseaseAnnotation a up:Disease_Annotation ;
                   up:disease ?disease .
  ?disease skos:prefLabel ?diseaseLabel .
  FILTER(regex(str(?diseaseLabel), "cancer", "i")) # Filter diseases by label containing "cancer"

  # Get the preferred name of the human gene encoded by the protein
  ?humanProtein up:encodedBy ?humanGene .
  ?humanGene skos:prefLabel ?humanGeneName .

  # Get the OrthoDB orthogroup URI for the human protein
  ?humanProtein rdfs:seeAlso ?orthoGroup .
  FILTER(STRSTARTS(STR(?orthoGroup), "http://purl.orthodb.org/odbgroup/")) # Ensure the xref is an OrthoDB group

  # Use the OrthoDB service to find members of the orthogroup
  SERVICE <https://sparql.orthodb.org/sparql/> {
    ?orthoGroup orthodb:hasMember ?orthoMember .
    # Get the UniProt xref for each member in the orthogroup
    ?orthoMember orthodb:xref/orthodb:xrefResource ?ratProtein .
  }

  # Use the UniProt service to check if the ortholog is from Rattus norvegicus
  # and get its Ensembl gene identifier
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql/> {
     ?ratProtein a up:Protein ;
                 up:organism taxon:10116 . # Rattus norvegicus

     # Get the gene encoded by the rat protein
     ?ratProtein up:encodedBy ?ratGene .
     # Get the Ensembl gene xref for the rat gene
     ?ratGene rdfs:seeAlso ?ensemblGene .
     FILTER(STRSTARTS(STR(?ensemblGene), "http://rdf.ebi.ac.uk/resource/ensembl/")) # Ensure the xref is an Ensembl gene
  }

  # Use the Bgee service to check if the Rattus norvegicus gene is expressed in the brain
  SERVICE <https://www.bgee.org/sparql/> {
    # Find the Bgee gene corresponding to the Ensembl gene identifier
    ?bgeeGene lscr:xrefEnsemblGene ?ensemblGene .

    # Check for expression in an anatomic entity labeled "brain"
    ?bgeeGene genex:isExpressedIn ?brainEntity .
    ?brainEntity rdfs:label "brain" . # Filter for the brain tissue
  }
}

natural_language_question: Find mouse homologs in OMABrowser of human enzymes that catalyze reactions involving sterols (CHEBI:15889). Federating with Rhea and OMABrowser.
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX lscr: <http://purl.org/lscr#>
PREFIX orth: <http://purl.org/net/orth#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>

SELECT
  DISTINCT
    ?chebi
    ?reaction
    ?humanProtein
    ?mouseProtein
    ?cluster 
WHERE {
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
    ?reaction rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound ?compound .
    ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi .
    ?chebi rdfs:subClassOf* CHEBI:15889
  }

  ?humanProtein up:organism taxon:9606 .
  ?humanProtein up:annotation ?a .
  ?a a up:Catalytic_Activity_Annotation .
  ?a up:catalyticActivity ?ca .
  ?ca up:catalyzedReaction ?reaction .

  SERVICE  <https://sparql.omabrowser.org/sparql> {
    ?cluster a orth:ParalogsCluster .
    ?cluster orth:hasHomologousMember ?node1 , ?node2 .
    ?node1 orth:hasHomologousMember* ?orthoProtein1 .
    ?node2 orth:hasHomologousMember* ?orthoProtein2 .
    ?orthoProtein1 lscr:xrefUniprot ?mouseProtein .
    ?orthoProtein2 lscr:xrefUniprot ?humanProtein .
    # inTaxon mouse
    ?orthoProtein1 orth:organism/<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002162> taxon:10090 . 
  }
}

  ?protein a up:Protein ;
           up:organism taxon:9606 ; # Human taxonomy ID

  ?catActivityAnnotation a up:Catalytic_Activity_Annotation ;

natural_language_question: Proteins with binding sites for ligands similar to heme
predicted_query:
# Primary endpoint: https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql/
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX sachem: <http://bioinfo.uochb.cas.cz/rdf/v1.0/sachem#>
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>

SELECT DISTINCT ?protein ?ligandName
WHERE {
  # Find proteins with binding site annotations in UniProt
  ?protein up:annotation ?annotation .
  ?annotation a up:Binding_Site_Annotation .

  # Get the ligand associated with the binding site
  ?annotation up:ligand ?ligand .
  ?ligand rdfs:subClassOf ?chebi . # Link ligand to its ChEBI identifier
  ?ligand rdfs:label ?ligandName . # Get the ligand name

  # Use the IDSM Sachem service to find ChEBI compounds similar to Heme (CHEBI:24867)
  # The SMILES for Heme B (CHEBI:24867) is used for the similarity search.
  SERVICE <https://idsm.elixir-czech.cz/sparql/endpoint/chebi> {
    ?similarChebi sachem:similarCompoundSearch [
      sachem:query "C[C@@H]1C=C(C)C2=C(C=C3C(C)=C(C=C4C(C)=C(C=C1[N+]2=C4)[N]5=C(C=C(C=C5)[N]6=C3C=C(C=C6)[N]7=C(C=C(C=C7)[Fe]))C(=O)O)C(=O)O"
      # Optional: Add sachem:threshold property to specify similarity threshold (default is often 0.8)
      # sachem:threshold "0.8"^^xsd:float
    ] .
  }

  # Filter the proteins whose ligand's ChEBI identifier matches one found by the similarity search
  FILTER(?chebi = ?similarChebi)
}

natural_language_question: Connect patents cited in UniProtKB with those in the patent database at EPO via publication number, whose grant date is more than twenty years in the past.
predicted_query:
# Primary endpoint: https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql/
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX patent: <http://data.epo.org/linked-data/def/patent/>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX fn: <http://www.w3.org/2005/xpath-functions#>

SELECT ?citation ?patentURI ?applicationNo ?grantDate
WHERE
{
  # Get patent citations from UniProtKB
  ?citation a up:Patent_Citation ;
            skos:exactMatch ?patentURI .

  # Extract the publication number from the patent URI.
  # This extraction method (SUBSTR) is based on the structure of EPO patent URIs
  # found in UniProtKB cross-references, e.g., http://data.epo.org/linked-data/data/publication/EP/1234567/A1
  BIND(SUBSTR(STR(?patentURI), 35) AS ?applicationNo)

  # Calculate the date exactly 20 years ago from the current date.
  # fn:adjust-date-to-timezone is used to handle potential timezone issues with NOW().
  BIND(fn:adjust-date-to-timezone(NOW(), "PT0H") - "P20Y"^^xsd:duration AS ?dateTwentyYearsAgo)

  # Query the EPO patent database using a SERVICE clause
  SERVICE <https://data.epo.org/linked-data/query>
  {
    # Find the patent application/publication by its number
    ?application patent:publicationNumber ?applicationNo ;
                 # Get the grant date for the patent
                 patent:grantDate ?grantDate .

    # Filter for patents where the grant date is more than twenty years in the past
    FILTER(?grantDate < ?dateTwentyYearsAgo)
  }
}

natural_language_question: Retrieve drugs that target human enzymes involved in sterol metabolism (federated query with WikiData and Rhea).
predicted_query:
# Primary endpoint: https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql/
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX wdt: <http://www.wikidata.org/prop/direct/>
PREFIX wd: <http://www.wikidata.org/entity/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?drug ?drugLabel ?protein ?proteinLabel
WHERE {
  # Find human proteins in UniProt
  ?protein a up:Protein ;
           up:organism taxon:9606 ; # Homo sapiens
           rdfs:label ?proteinLabel . # Get protein label from UniProt

  # Find catalytic activity annotations for these proteins
  ?protein up:annotation ?a .
  ?a a up:Catalytic_Activity_Annotation ;
    up:catalyticActivity ?ca .

  # Find the reactions catalyzed by these activities
  ?ca up:catalyzedReaction ?reaction .

  # Federate with Rhea to check if the reaction involves sterols
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    # Ensure ?reaction is a specific reaction instance
    ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
    # Check if the reaction involves a compound that is a sterol or a subclass of sterol
    ?reaction rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound/rh:chebi ?chebi .
    ?chebi rdfs:subClassOf* CHEBI:15889 . # CHEBI:15889 is 'sterol'
  }

  # Federate with WikiData to find drugs targeting these proteins
  SERVICE <https://query.wikidata.org/sparql> {
    # Get the UniProt ID from the protein URI to link with WikiData
    BIND(STRAFTER(STR(?protein), "http://purl.uniprot.org/uniprot/") AS ?uniprotId)

    # Find entities in WikiData that are instances of drug
    ?drug wdt:P31 wd:Q12140 . # Q12140 is 'drug'

    # Find entities in WikiData that target a protein with the matching UniProt ID
    ?drug wdt:P129 ?targetProtein . # P129 is 'targets'
    ?targetProtein wdt:P352 ?uniprotId . # P352 is 'UniProt ID'

    # Get the label for the drug in English
    ?drug rdfs:label ?drugLabel .
    FILTER(LANG(?drugLabel) = "en")
  }
}

natural_language_question: Connect patents cited in UniProtKB with those in the patent database at EPO via publication number.

SELECT ?uniprotCitation ?epoPublication ?publicationNumber
WHERE
{
  # Find patent citations in UniProtKB
  ?uniprotCitation a up:Patent_Citation ;
                   # Link to the patent URI (often in the EPO linked data format)
                   skos:exactMatch ?patentURI .

  # Extract the publication number from the patent URI
  # Assumes a URI structure like http://data.epo.org/linked-data/patent/COUNTRY/NUMBER/KIND

  SERVICE <https://data.epo.org/linked-data/query>

    # Find the patent publication in the EPO database using the publication number
    ?epoPublication patent:publicationNumber ?publicationNumber .
    # We could add more details from EPO here if needed, e.g., patent:application ?application .

natural_language_question: Find human proteins that catalyze reactions where substrates or product have a Cholestane skeleton
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX sachem: <http://bioinfo.uochb.cas.cz/rdf/v1.0/sachem#>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>

SELECT
  DISTINCT
    ?protein
    ?disease
    ?rhea
    ?chebi
    ?omim
WHERE {
    # Find complete ChEBIs with a Cholestane skeleton, via the Czech Elixir node IDSM Sachem chemical substructure search.
    SERVICE <https://idsm.elixir-czech.cz/sparql/endpoint/chebi> {
      ?chebi sachem:substructureSearch [
        sachem:query
"[C@]12(CCC3CCCC[C@]3(C)[C@@]1([H])CC[C@]1(C)[C@@]([H])([C@@](C)([H])CCCC(C)C)CC[C@@]21[H])[H]"
].
   }
   # Use the fact that UniProt catalytic activities are annotated using Rhea 
   # Mapping the found ChEBIs to Rhea reactions
   SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql>{
     ?rhea rh:side/rh:contains/rh:compound/rdfs:subClassOf ?chebi .
   }
   # Match the found Rhea reactions with human UniProtKB proteins
   ?protein up:annotation/up:catalyticActivity/up:catalyzedReaction ?rhea .
   ?protein up:organism taxon:9606 .
   # Find only those human entries that have an annotated related disease, and optionaly map these to OMIM
   ?protein up:annotation/up:disease ?disease .
   OPTIONAL {
     ?disease rdfs:seeAlso ?omim .
     ?omim up:database <http://purl.uniprot.org/database/MIM>
   }
}

natural_language_question: For the human entry P05067 (Amyloid-beta precursor protein) find the gene start ends in WikiData
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql/
PREFIX uniprotkb: <http://purl.uniprot.org/uniprot/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX wdt: <http://www.wikidata.org/prop/direct/>

SELECT ?gene ?geneStart ?geneEnd
WHERE {
  # Start from the UniProt entry for P05067
  uniprotkb:P05067 rdfs:seeAlso ?wikidataItem .

  # Filter to ensure the seeAlso link is to WikiData
  FILTER(STRSTARTS(STR(?wikidataItem), "http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q"))

  # Query the WikiData endpoint using SERVICE
  SERVICE <https://query.wikidata.org/sparql> {
    # Find the gene encoded by the protein (or associated with the protein item)
    # P702 is the WikiData property "encoded by"
    ?wikidataItem wdt:P702 ?gene .

    # Retrieve the genomic start and end positions for the gene
    # P644 is "genomic start"
    # P645 is "genomic end"
    ?gene wdt:P644 ?geneStart ;
          wdt:P645 ?geneEnd .
  }
}

natural_language_question: Which are the proteins associated with glioblastoma and the orthologs expressed in the rat brain?
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql/
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX orthodb: <http://purl.orthodb.org/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?ratOrthologProtein ?ratOrthologProteinName ?glioblastomaProtein ?glioblastomaProteinName
WHERE {
  # Find proteins associated with Glioblastoma in UniProt
  # We search for the disease label "glioblastoma" as it's a specific type of glioma
  ?glioblastomaProtein up:annotation ?diseaseAnnotation .
  ?diseaseAnnotation a up:Disease_Annotation ;
                   up:disease ?disease .
  ?disease skos:prefLabel ?diseaseLabel .
  FILTER (CONTAINS(LCASE(?diseaseLabel), "glioblastoma"))

  # Get the name of the glioblastoma protein (optional)
  OPTIONAL { ?glioblastomaProtein up:recommendedName/up:fullName ?glioblastomaProteinName . }
  OPTIONAL { ?glioblastomaProtein up:submittedName/up:fullName ?glioblastomaProteinName . }

  # Find the ortholog group for the glioblastoma protein using rdfs:seeAlso
  ?glioblastomaProtein rdfs:seeAlso ?orthoGroup .
  # Ensure the seeAlso link points to an OrthoDB resource
  FILTER (STRSTARTS(STR(?orthoGroup), "http://purl.orthodb.org/"))

  # Use SERVICE to query OrthoDB for members of this ortholog group
  SERVICE <https://sparql.orthodb.org/sparql> {
    # Find members of the ortholog group
    ?orthoGroup orthodb:hasMember ?orthoMember .
    # Get the external reference (xref) for the member
    ?orthoMember orthodb:xref ?orthoMemberXref .
    # Get the resource URI (UniProt URI) from the xref
    ?orthoMemberXref orthodb:xrefResource ?ratOrthologProteinUri .
  }

  # Back in UniProt, check the ortholog member identified from OrthoDB
  # Bind the URI string obtained from OrthoDB to a URI variable
  BIND(URI(?ratOrthologProteinUri) AS ?ratOrthologProtein)

  # Filter the ortholog protein by organism: Rat (Rattus norvegicus, taxon:10116)
  ?ratOrthologProtein up:organism taxon:10116 .

  # Get the name of the rat ortholog protein (optional)
  OPTIONAL { ?ratOrthologProtein up:recommendedName/up:fullName ?ratOrthologProteinName . }
  OPTIONAL { ?ratOrthologProtein up:submittedName/up:fullName ?ratOrthologProteinName . }

  # Check for expression annotation in the rat ortholog protein
  # Filter for comments that mention "brain" to indicate expression in brain tissue
  ?ratOrthologProtein up:annotation ?expressionAnnotation .
  ?expressionAnnotation a up:Expression_Annotation ;
                      rdfs:comment ?expressionComment .
  FILTER (CONTAINS(LCASE(?expressionComment), "brain"))
}

natural_language_question: Rabbit's proteins encoded by genes that are orthologous to Mouse's HBB-Y gene and their cross reference links to Uniprot
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX lscr: <http://purl.org/lscr#>
PREFIX orth: <http://purl.org/net/orth#>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
SELECT DISTINCT ?PROTEIN_1 ?PROTEIN_2 ?UNIPROT_XREF_1 ?UNIPROT_XREF_2 WHERE {
	?taxon_1 up:commonName 'Mouse' .
	?taxon_2 up:commonName 'Rabbit' .
	SERVICE <https://sparql.omabrowser.org/sparql/> {
		?cluster a orth:OrthologsCluster .
		?cluster orth:hasHomologousMember ?node1 .
		?cluster orth:hasHomologousMember ?node2 .
		?node2 orth:hasHomologousMember* ?PROTEIN_2 .
		?node1 orth:hasHomologousMember* ?PROTEIN_1 .
		?PROTEIN_1 a orth:Protein .
		?PROTEIN_1 orth:organism/obo:RO_0002162 ?taxon_1 ;
			rdfs:label 'HBB-Y' ;
			lscr:xrefUniprot ?UNIPROT_XREF_1 .
		?PROTEIN_2 a orth:Protein .
		?PROTEIN_2 orth:organism/obo:RO_0002162 ?taxon_2 .
		?PROTEIN_2 lscr:xrefUniprot ?UNIPROT_XREF_2 .
		FILTER ( ?node1 != ?node2 )
	}
}

  # Define taxon IDs for Mouse (Mus musculus) and Rabbit (Oryctolagus cuniculus)
  BIND(taxon:10090 AS ?mouseTaxon)

  ?mouseGene a up:Gene ;
             up:organism ?mouseTaxon ;
             skos:prefLabel "HBB-Y" . # Assuming "HBB-Y" is the preferred label for the gene

  # 2. Find the protein encoded by the Mouse gene
  ?mouseProtein up:encodedBy ?mouseGene .

  # 3. Find the OrthoDB group linked to the Mouse protein via rdfs:seeAlso
  ?mouseProtein rdfs:seeAlso ?orthoGroup .
  FILTER(STRSTARTS(STR(?orthoGroup), "http://purl.orthodb.org/")) # Ensure the linked resource is from OrthoDB

  # 4. Use the OrthoDB service to find members of this orthologous group
  SERVICE <https://sparql.orthodb.org/sparql> {
    ?orthoGroup orthodb:hasMember ?orthoMemberId .
    # Link the OrthoDB member ID back to its UniProt resource URI
    ?orthoMemberId orthodb:xref/orthodb:xrefResource ?rabbitProtein .
  }

  # 5. Back in UniProt, filter the orthologous members to be from Rabbit
  ?rabbitProtein up:organism ?rabbitTaxon .

  # 6. Find the gene encoding the Rabbit protein

  BIND(STRAFTER(STR(?rabbitProtein), "http://purl.uniprot.org/uniprot/") AS ?rabbitProteinAccession)

natural_language_question: Distribution of reactions according to the first class of the enzyme classification (federated query)

PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>

# Query 11
# Retrieve the count of reactions mapped to each level (main class) of the enzyme classification
#
# This query mimics the Filter section of the Rhea website (Browse all reactions)
# https://www.rhea-db.org/rhea?query=
SELECT ?ecClass (STR(?ecName) AS ?ecClassName) (COUNT(?rhea) AS ?rheaCount)
WHERE {
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    VALUES (?ecClass) { (ec:1.-.-.-)(ec:2.-.-.-)(ec:3.-.-.-)(ec:4.-.-.-)(ec:5.-.-.-) (ec:6.-.-.-) (ec:7.-.-.-)}
    ?ecNumber rdfs:subClassOf ?ecClass .
    ?ecClass skos:prefLabel ?ecName .
  }
  ?rhea rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
  ?rhea rh:ec ?ecNumber .
} GROUP BY ?ecClass ?ecName

    VALUES (?ecClass) {
      (ec:1.-.-.-) # Oxidoreductases
      (ec:2.-.-.-) # Transferases
      (ec:3.-.-.-) # Hydrolases
      (ec:4.-.-.-) # Lyases
      (ec:5.-.-.-) # Isomerases
      (ec:6.-.-.-) # Ligases
      (ec:7.-.-.-) # Translocases
    }
    # Find EC numbers that are subclasses of these first level classes
    ?ecNumber rdfs:subClassOf ?ecClass .
    # Get the preferred label for the first level class
    ?ecClass skos:prefLabel ?ecName .
  }
}
# Group results by the first level EC class and its name to count reactions per class
GROUP BY ?ecClass ?ecName
ORDER BY ?ecClass

natural_language_question: Select all Rhea reactions linked to protein sequences (enzymes and transporters) in UniProtKB
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>

# Query 12
# Select all Rhea reactions used to annotate enzyme sequences in UniProtKB
# return the number of UniProtKB entries
# Federated query using a service to UniProt SPARQL endpoint
#
# This query corresponds to the Rhea website query:
# https://www.rhea-db.org/rhea?query=uniprot:*
#
SELECT ?uniprotCount ?rhea ?accession ?equation 
WHERE {
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> { 
  	SELECT ?rhea (count(?uniprot) as ?uniprotCount) {
      ?uniprot up:annotation/up:catalyticActivity/up:catalyzedReaction ?rhea . 
  	}
  	GROUP BY ?rhea
  }
  ?rhea rh:accession ?accession .
  ?rhea rh:equation ?equation .
}

natural_language_question: Generate a draft human metabolome
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxon: <http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>

SELECT DISTINCT ?chebi ?chebiLabel
WHERE {
  # Query UniProt to find human proteins that are enzymes
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    ?protein a up:Protein .
    ?protein up:organism taxon:9606 . # Filter for human proteins

    # Find catalytic activity annotations for these proteins
    ?protein up:annotation ?a .
    ?a a up:Catalytic_Activity_Annotation .
    ?a up:catalyticActivity ?ca .

    # Link the catalytic activity to a Rhea reaction
    ?ca up:catalyzedReaction ?reaction . # ?reaction will be a Rhea URI
  }

  # Query Rhea to find metabolites involved in these reactions
  SERVICE <https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql> {
    # Use the Rhea reaction URI obtained from UniProt
    ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction . # Ensure it's a valid Rhea reaction

    # Find the reaction sides (substrates/products)
    ?reaction rh:side ?reactionSide .

    # Find the participants (compounds) in the reaction sides
    ?reactionSide rh:contains ?participant .

    # Find the compound associated with the participant
    ?participant rh:compound ?compound .

    # Get the ChEBI identifier for the compound
    ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi .
  }

  # Optional: Query a public ChEBI endpoint to get the label for the metabolite
  # Note: This service is not explicitly listed in the context but is commonly used for ontology lookups.
  SERVICE <https://sparql.ebi.ac.uk/sparql> {
      ?chebi rdfs:label ?chebiLabel .
  }
}

natural_language_question: Search for Chemical names starting in Japanese, translated to english using allie
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql/
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX chebi: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>

SELECT ?chebi ?japaneseLabel ?englishLabel
WHERE {
  # Find chemical compounds in Rhea DB.
  # Rhea links its compounds to ChEBI identifiers.
  ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi .

  # Get the standard label for the ChEBI entity.
  # This label is typically in English and will be used to link to ALLIE.
  ?chebi rdfs:label ?chebiName .

  # Use the ALLIE service to find entities that have the ChEBI name as an English label
  # and also have a Japanese label.
  SERVICE <https://data.allie.dbcls.jp/sparql> {
    # Find an entity ?x in ALLIE that has ?chebiName as an English label.
    ?x rdfs:label ?englishLabel .
    FILTER(STR(?englishLabel) = STR(?chebiName) && lang(?englishLabel) = "en")

    # Find the corresponding Japanese label for the same entity ?x in ALLIE.
    ?x rdfs:label ?japaneseLabel .
    FILTER(lang(?japaneseLabel) = "ja")
  }
}

natural_language_question: Retrieve parent reactions (and their catalyzing enzymes) for a metabolite that is not directly involved in a reaction (ex: CHEBI:83137).
ground_truth_query:
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rh:<http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX ec:<http://purl.uniprot.org/enzyme/>
PREFIX up:<http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>
PREFIX taxon:<http://purl.uniprot.org/taxonomy/>
PREFIX keywords:<http://purl.uniprot.org/keywords/>

SELECT
  ?chebi
  ?ecNumber
  (count(?protein) as ?proteinCount)
  ?reaction
  ?equation
WHERE {
  ?reaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
  ?reaction rh:status rh:Approved .
  ?reaction rh:equation ?equation .
  ?reaction rh:ec ?ecNumber .
  ?reaction rh:side ?reactionSide .
  ?reactionSide rh:contains ?participant .
  ?participant rh:compound ?compound .
  ?compound rh:chebi ?chebi .
  CHEBI:83137 rdfs:subClassOf+ ?chebi.

  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
  ?protein a up:Protein .
  ?protein up:reviewed true .
    {?protein up:enzyme ?ecNumber}
  UNION
    {?protein up:domain/up:enzyme ?ecNumber}
  UNION
    {?protein up:component/up:enzyme ?ecNumber} .
  }
} 
GROUP BY ?chebi ?ecNumber ?reaction ?equation
predicted_query:
# https://sparql.rhea-db.org/sparql/
PREFIX rh: <http://rdf.rhea-db.org/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX CHEBI: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_>
PREFIX up: <http://purl.uniprot.org/core/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?parentReaction ?ecNumber ?protein
WHERE {
  # Find reactions (child reactions) that involve the specified metabolite (CHEBI:83137)
  ?childReaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction .
  ?childReaction rh:status rh:Approved . # Ensure the child reaction is approved
  ?childReaction rh:side ?side .
  ?side rh:contains ?participant .
  ?participant rh:compound ?compound .
  ?compound rh:chebi CHEBI:83137 . # Link to the specific metabolite

  # Find the parent reaction(s) of the child reaction
  ?childReaction rdfs:subClassOf ?parentReaction .
  ?parentReaction rdfs:subClassOf rh:Reaction . # Ensure the parent is a Rhea reaction
  ?parentReaction rh:status rh:Approved . # Ensure the parent reaction is approved

  # Find the EC number(s) associated with the parent reaction
  ?parentReaction rh:ec ?ecNumber .

  # Federate to UniProt to find proteins associated with the EC number
  SERVICE <https://sparql.uniprot.org/sparql> {
    ?protein a up:Protein .
    # Link protein to EC number (considering different ways EC is linked in UniProt)
    { ?protein up:enzyme ?ecNumber }
    UNION
    { ?protein up:domain/up:enzyme ?ecNumber }
    UNION
    { ?protein up:component/up:enzyme ?ecNumber }
  }
}
